Dogan Holding, Dogan Yayin, Tupras: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-04-04T06:45:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/dogan-holding-dogan-yayin-tupras-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active
in  Turkey . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the
last close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  rose 1,279.89, or
2 percent, to 65,714.40 on April 1.  Coca-Cola Icecek AS (CCOLA)  : The Turkish bottler of coke
drinks had its price estimate raised to 21.6 liras from 19.8
liras at Citigroup Inc., according to a report today. Coca-Cola
Icecek gained 65 kurus, or 3.4 percent, to 20 liras.  Dogan Sirketler Grubu Holding AS (DOHOL TI): The Turkish
group with interests in media and energy, returned to profit
with a full-year net income of 656.2 million liras ($429
million) in 2010, compared with a loss of 114.1 million liras in
2009, it said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange . The
2010 profit exceeded an average estimate of 191 million liras in
a Bloomberg survey of five analysts. Dogan Holding climbed 2
kurus, or 1.7 percent, to 1.22 liras.  Dogan Yayin Holding AS (DYHOL)  : Turkey’s biggest media
group’s full-year loss narrowed to 237 million liras from 343
million liras in 2009, it said in a statement to the bourse
after the market closed on April 1. The company was expected to
report a loss of 70.5 million liras, according to the average
estimate of six analysts in a Bloomberg survey. Dogan Yayin
advanced 5 kurus, or 2.5 percent, to 2.03 liras.  Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS (FROTO)  : The Turkish unit of
Ford Motor Co. in partnership with Koc Holding AS will invest
205 million euros ($292 million) to produce a new van model at
its Kocaeli plant in northwestern Turkey, it said in a statement
to the bourse after the market closed on April 1. Ford Otosan
fell 1 lira, or 6.8 percent, to 13.75 liras.  Tupras Turkiye Petrol Rafinerileri AS (TUPRS)  : Turkey’s
sole oil refiner was cut to “underperform” from “neutral” at
Bank of America Corp., according to a report today. Tupras
gained 70 kurus, or 1.5 percent, to 46.1 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
